Image Description: Digital Literacy Essentials Infographic

This vertical infographic, titled "Digital Literacy Essentials," uses a clean, four-quadrant layout with soft pastel colors (green, blue, red, and orange) to explain the core components of navigating the digital world effectively.

1. What Digital Literacy Is (Green Section)
Located at the top left, this section defines the term with an icon of an open book and a cursor. Key points include:

The ability to find, evaluate, and communicate information using digital platforms.

Applying critical thinking to digital content.

Adapting to new technologies as they emerge.

2. Useful Digital Tools for Students (Blue Section)
Located at the top right, this section lists essential productivity apps accompanied by their logos:

Google Calendar: Used for organization.

Evernote: Used for note-taking.

Google Docs: Used for real-time collaboration.

3. Safe Internet Practices (Red & Orange Sections)
The bottom half of the graphic focuses on digital safety and security, represented by a shield icon with a padlock. It repeats three core pillars of online safety:

Use strong, unique passwords: To protect accounts from unauthorized access.

Be cautious with personal information: Avoiding oversharing sensitive data.

Verify sources before sharing: Preventing the spread of misinformation by checking facts first.
